1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:05,171
[Azuelo] <i>After a thorough investigation,</i>
<i>the result is clear.</i>

2
00:00:05,255 --> 00:00:10,468
<i>Datu Rahman was used</i>
<i>as a fall guy by the syndicate</i>

3
00:00:10,552 --> 00:00:14,014
<i>so they can continue</i>
<i>their illegal operations</i>

4
00:00:14,097 --> 00:00:16,099
<i>in our country.</i>

5
00:00:16,182 --> 00:00:17,600
- [Espina] <i>What if this is a setup?</i>
- [Marcus] <i>But who?</i>

6
00:00:17,684 --> 00:00:19,978
[Espina] <i>I have a hunch,</i>
<i>but I'm not sure yet.</i>

7
00:00:20,061 --> 00:00:22,939
[Marcus] I don't have proof yet,
but I think it's…

8
00:00:23,022 --> 00:00:24,899
- General Carillo.
- General Carillo.

9
00:00:24,983 --> 00:00:26,151
[Azuelo] <i>You have completely lost it!</i>

10
00:00:26,234 --> 00:00:28,069
<i>He is highly respected by everyone.</i>

11
00:00:28,153 --> 00:00:33,366
How could he conspire
against the agency he built?

12
00:00:33,450 --> 00:00:37,037
[reporter 1] <i>Datu Rahman</i>
<i>is officially being released</i>

13
00:00:37,120 --> 00:00:40,790
<i>after being acquitted</i>
<i>of all charges against him.</i>

14
00:00:40,874 --> 00:00:44,210
<i>Authorities are stopping</i>
<i>the search for Jalil Abubakar,</i>

15
00:00:44,294 --> 00:00:45,670
<i>son of Datu Rahman Abubakar,</i>

16
00:00:45,754 --> 00:00:48,381
<i>after it was determined</i>

17
00:00:48,465 --> 00:00:50,925
<i>that the allegations</i>
<i>against him were false.</i>

18
00:00:51,009 --> 00:00:53,052
[Espina] <i>If our suspicions are right,</i>

19
00:00:53,136 --> 00:00:56,389
<i>the victims of Damai Island</i>
<i>never received justice.</i>

20
00:00:56,473 --> 00:00:57,932
[Marcus] We need to end this.

21
00:00:58,016 --> 00:01:02,228
I refuse to let my comrades'
deaths be in vain.

22
00:01:02,312 --> 00:01:04,397
[intense music playing]

23
00:01:06,191 --> 00:01:11,529
[mysterious theme music playing]

24
00:01:21,331 --> 00:01:23,249
[in Arabic] Praise be to God.

25
00:01:24,626 --> 00:01:26,628
At last, the truth has come to light.

26
00:01:27,212 --> 00:01:29,714
Datu Rahman no longer has to hide.

27
00:01:29,798 --> 00:01:31,424
[gentle music playing]

28
00:01:31,508 --> 00:01:34,594
Jamilah, does that mean

29
00:01:34,677 --> 00:01:38,723
we can go back to the island with Jalil?

30
00:01:41,184 --> 00:01:44,521
That's right, Sitti. [giggles] Come here.

31
00:01:46,397 --> 00:01:48,483
[Norhana] That's sad news for me.

32
00:01:50,110 --> 00:01:51,694
I'm going to miss you.

33
00:01:51,778 --> 00:01:53,655
[Omar and Norhana chuckles]

34
00:01:53,738 --> 00:01:55,949
But, you know, I'm really happy

35
00:01:56,032 --> 00:02:01,121
because you'll finally be
with your family.

36
00:02:01,996 --> 00:02:04,249
But I'll miss you so much.

37
00:02:04,332 --> 00:02:06,000
[Omar and Jamilah chuckling]

38
00:02:06,084 --> 00:02:10,004
[poignant music playing]

39
00:02:13,466 --> 00:02:16,427
Due to the confession of the suspects

40
00:02:16,511 --> 00:02:18,680
and the speedy investigation

41
00:02:18,763 --> 00:02:22,225
of Presidential Chief of Staff
Ahmad Mustapha,

42
00:02:22,308 --> 00:02:25,478
Datu Rahman was proven innocent.

43
00:02:25,562 --> 00:02:28,064
I hope this is where it all ends.

44
00:02:28,148 --> 00:02:31,109
Because if there is one thing
that we've learned

45
00:02:31,192 --> 00:02:33,486
from the tragedy on Damai Island,

46
00:02:33,570 --> 00:02:37,907
it is the realization
that peace is not only precious,

47
00:02:37,991 --> 00:02:39,951
it's also very fragile.

48
00:02:40,034 --> 00:02:43,413
Especially when greed prevails.

49
00:02:44,873 --> 00:02:47,125
[in English] In our next episode,

50
00:02:47,208 --> 00:02:49,377
we will dig even deeper.

51
00:02:49,460 --> 00:02:51,087
We will interview

52
00:02:51,170 --> 00:02:54,841
Presidential Chief of Staff Ahmad Mustapha

53
00:02:54,924 --> 00:02:58,386
and retired Police General Manuel Carillo.

54
00:02:58,469 --> 00:03:01,681
[in English] And they will talk about
the country's next steps

55
00:03:01,764 --> 00:03:04,851
toward solving the gun problem
in the Philippines

56
00:03:04,934 --> 00:03:06,436
once and for all.

57
00:03:07,270 --> 00:03:08,313
[in English] Listen up!

58
00:03:08,396 --> 00:03:11,190
I have two major announcements

59
00:03:11,274 --> 00:03:12,775
from the higher-ups.

60
00:03:13,401 --> 00:03:16,821
First, three days from now,

61
00:03:16,905 --> 00:03:19,908
a high-level conference will take place

62
00:03:19,991 --> 00:03:23,202
for the Japanese investment deal.

63
00:03:23,286 --> 00:03:27,749
General Manuel Carillo
personally requested

64
00:03:27,832 --> 00:03:33,463
that Task Force Alpha provide security

65
00:03:33,546 --> 00:03:38,760
to the Japanese investors
and Filipino delegates.

66
00:03:40,720 --> 00:03:44,307
Task Force Alpha was also assigned

67
00:03:44,390 --> 00:03:46,851
to escort the Japanese delegation,

68
00:03:46,935 --> 00:03:49,354
from the moment they land at the airport

69
00:03:49,437 --> 00:03:52,440
until they arrive at the venue.

70
00:03:53,900 --> 00:03:55,568
With all due respect, sir,

71
00:03:56,903 --> 00:03:59,614
since when did Task Force Alpha
become a security detail?

72
00:04:01,115 --> 00:04:03,868
[in English] We are
a specialized tactical unit, sir.

73
00:04:04,619 --> 00:04:06,371
We are not bodyguards.

74
00:04:06,454 --> 00:04:08,373
[tense music playing]

75
00:04:10,959 --> 00:04:14,545
[in English] I'm sorry. But as head agent,
I have to agree with Agent Reyes.

76
00:04:14,629 --> 00:04:16,547
I understand your sentiments.

77
00:04:17,674 --> 00:04:24,180
[in English] But Task Force Alpha
is the best of the best!

78
00:04:24,264 --> 00:04:25,723
Aren't you?

79
00:04:26,349 --> 00:04:29,727
That's why General Carillo
personally requested you

80
00:04:29,811 --> 00:04:32,105
to make sure this will go smoothly

81
00:04:32,188 --> 00:04:35,566
because this operation is sensitive.

82
00:04:36,317 --> 00:04:39,153
There is a lot at stake.

83
00:04:39,237 --> 00:04:44,409
The whole country is counting
on this investment deal.

84
00:04:44,492 --> 00:04:47,829
[in English] We cannot let them down.

85
00:04:48,913 --> 00:04:49,872
[in English] Understood?

86
00:04:49,956 --> 00:04:51,582
- [in English] Sir, yes, sir!
- [in English] Sir, yes, sir!

87
00:04:52,250 --> 00:04:53,209
[Azuelo, in English] Good.

88
00:04:53,293 --> 00:04:56,963
And for my second announcement,

89
00:04:57,046 --> 00:05:02,719
Chief of Staff Ahmad Mustapha
will be here today

90
00:05:02,802 --> 00:05:08,850
to oversee Datu Rahman Abubakar's
formal release

91
00:05:08,933 --> 00:05:12,270
and the signing of legal documents.

92
00:05:13,104 --> 00:05:14,814
We all know

93
00:05:14,897 --> 00:05:17,650
that even though
Datu Rahman has been cleared,

94
00:05:17,734 --> 00:05:21,195
his life is still in danger.

95
00:05:21,279 --> 00:05:24,741
So we must protect him
while he's under NLEA custody.

96
00:05:24,824 --> 00:05:29,329
His safety is our responsibility.

97
00:05:29,912 --> 00:05:31,998
- Is that clear?
- [all, in English] Sir, yes, sir!

98
00:05:32,665 --> 00:05:33,708
[in English] Good.

99
00:05:33,791 --> 00:05:35,418
[unsettling music playing]

100
00:05:44,343 --> 00:05:46,596
[music intensifies]

101
00:05:55,563 --> 00:05:57,398
[music concludes]

102
00:05:57,482 --> 00:05:58,441
[vehicle honking]

103
00:05:59,233 --> 00:06:01,778
Yes, Jamilah. We just got here.

104
00:06:01,861 --> 00:06:03,654
Where are you?

105
00:06:03,738 --> 00:06:06,532
Okay, well, hurry up. We'll wait for you.

106
00:06:07,366 --> 00:06:11,204
- Miss Norhana, where's Jamilah?
- She's coming.

107
00:06:11,287 --> 00:06:15,958
Uh, her colleagues
will accompany her. Let's go.

108
00:06:16,042 --> 00:06:18,669
I can't believe they're releasing
that Datu Rahman.

109
00:06:19,337 --> 00:06:21,047
No wonder there are so many people.

110
00:06:21,130 --> 00:06:23,216
Oh, boy. He's a Muslim.

111
00:06:23,299 --> 00:06:25,468
He'll definitely cause trouble
once released.

112
00:06:26,344 --> 00:06:27,303
Excuse me.

113
00:06:27,386 --> 00:06:30,556
Do you personally know
Datu Rahman to say that?

114
00:06:30,640 --> 00:06:32,058
I'm just telling the truth.

115
00:06:32,141 --> 00:06:34,310
Muslims are violent people.

116
00:06:34,393 --> 00:06:35,728
You always cause trouble.

117
00:06:35,812 --> 00:06:38,689
What did you say? How about I show you
how violent we are?

118
00:06:38,773 --> 00:06:40,024
- Huh?
- Rashid, Rashid, enough.

119
00:06:41,067 --> 00:06:45,655
We only fight back when we need to.

120
00:06:45,738 --> 00:06:47,448
We're not violent.

121
00:06:48,199 --> 00:06:49,784
We avoid trouble as much as we can.

122
00:06:51,327 --> 00:06:55,039
You're so quick to judge our people.

123
00:06:55,123 --> 00:06:57,917
You don't even know us.

124
00:06:58,000 --> 00:07:00,128
You don't know Muslims.

125
00:07:00,211 --> 00:07:03,339
Everything you know about us
comes from false information

126
00:07:03,422 --> 00:07:05,258
and harmful stereotypes.

127
00:07:05,341 --> 00:07:06,926
Am I right?

128
00:07:07,677 --> 00:07:09,470
Sorry. He didn't mean that.

129
00:07:09,554 --> 00:07:11,013
I'm sorry. It won't happen again.

130
00:07:11,639 --> 00:07:12,849
Thank you.

131
00:07:14,100 --> 00:07:15,476
Come on. Let's go.

132
00:07:15,560 --> 00:07:17,270
- Unbelievable.
- Come on.

133
00:07:17,353 --> 00:07:21,941
[morose music concludes]

134
00:07:22,024 --> 00:07:24,527
[suspenseful music playing]

135
00:07:24,610 --> 00:07:26,320
[camera shutters clicking]

136
00:07:34,245 --> 00:07:36,080
[music turns stirring]

137
00:07:54,557 --> 00:07:56,100
[stirring music continues]

138
00:08:14,911 --> 00:08:16,746
[camera shutters clicking]

139
00:08:28,925 --> 00:08:31,093
[music intensifies]

140
00:08:56,994 --> 00:08:59,080
[camera shutters clicking]

141
00:09:03,042 --> 00:09:05,044
[poignant music playing]

142
00:09:31,028 --> 00:09:32,196
Father!

143
00:09:32,280 --> 00:09:33,573
‪[music intensifies]

144
00:09:43,249 --> 00:09:46,168
Jamilah looks beautiful on TV.

145
00:09:51,966 --> 00:09:54,218
[poignant music playing]

146
00:10:03,853 --> 00:10:04,854
[in Tausug] Thank you.

147
00:10:05,855 --> 00:10:08,566
[in Arabic] God is great.
Peace be upon you.

148
00:10:08,649 --> 00:10:09,483
‪[gentle music playing]

149
00:10:12,486 --> 00:10:14,572
[in Arabic] Peace be upon you.
Peace be upon you.

150
00:10:16,866 --> 00:10:20,828
Director Azuelo. Thank you very much.

151
00:10:20,911 --> 00:10:24,498
Because of your cooperation,
it was a success.

152
00:10:24,582 --> 00:10:26,876
We just did our job, sir.

153
00:10:28,294 --> 00:10:31,464
[Ahmad] And of course,
thank you to you as well.

154
00:10:33,591 --> 00:10:34,842
Thank you so much.

155
00:10:36,469 --> 00:10:37,762
Thank you very much.

156
00:10:39,430 --> 00:10:40,848
Thank you so much.

157
00:10:40,931 --> 00:10:42,725
- [in Arabic] Peace be upon you.
- [in Arabic] And unto you peace.

158
00:10:42,808 --> 00:10:44,185
Thank you very much.

159
00:10:45,895 --> 00:10:47,146
Thank you so much.

160
00:10:47,229 --> 00:10:48,314
Marcus!

161
00:10:49,440 --> 00:10:50,900
Thank you so much, Marcus.

162
00:10:50,983 --> 00:10:52,360
Thank you, sir.

163
00:10:53,277 --> 00:10:54,695
Thank you so much.

164
00:10:56,530 --> 00:10:57,531
Thank you very much.

165
00:10:57,615 --> 00:10:59,200
[bright music playing]

166
00:11:00,201 --> 00:11:02,745
Sir, I think the threat
against the country and NLEA

167
00:11:03,496 --> 00:11:04,830
is still not completely over.

168
00:11:05,539 --> 00:11:07,541
It really isn't.

169
00:11:08,167 --> 00:11:10,836
We're just making them believe otherwise

170
00:11:10,920 --> 00:11:14,340
to get their plans sailing.

171
00:11:14,965 --> 00:11:16,717
What do you mean, sir?

172
00:11:19,720 --> 00:11:23,099
This… is what I mean.

173
00:11:25,601 --> 00:11:26,435
‪[dramatic sting]

174
00:11:28,854 --> 00:11:32,441
You're suspecting General Carillo as well?

175
00:11:35,319 --> 00:11:38,322
I don't have any evidence yet, but…

176
00:11:38,906 --> 00:11:42,451
based on the sophistication
of the syndicate,

177
00:11:43,536 --> 00:11:48,791
only General Carillo is capable
to do all of it.

178
00:11:49,375 --> 00:11:51,710
The connection, the capability…

179
00:11:52,420 --> 00:11:54,922
No one else, but him.

180
00:11:55,840 --> 00:11:59,677
Sir, I am also suspicious
of General Carillo.

181
00:12:01,220 --> 00:12:02,430
[smirks]

182
00:12:03,514 --> 00:12:06,725
I made the right choice
in choosing you, Jalil.

183
00:12:08,269 --> 00:12:10,896
Marcus suspects the same, sir.

184
00:12:10,980 --> 00:12:12,398
The only thing missing is an evidence.

185
00:12:12,481 --> 00:12:15,067
[tense music playing]

186
00:12:15,151 --> 00:12:16,694
[sighs heavily]

187
00:12:16,777 --> 00:12:21,949
General Carillo is smart and clever.

188
00:12:22,032 --> 00:12:25,286
He was able to gain
the trust of the president.

189
00:12:25,870 --> 00:12:29,832
That's why we can't just
suspect him carelessly.

190
00:12:30,416 --> 00:12:33,085
We only have one chance.

191
00:12:33,169 --> 00:12:36,547
And when we hit him,
it should be bullseye.

192
00:12:38,799 --> 00:12:43,429
We need to knock General Carillo down.

193
00:12:43,512 --> 00:12:45,639
Because if not,

194
00:12:47,391 --> 00:12:48,976
he'll get away with it.

195
00:12:50,603 --> 00:12:52,354
We'll never be able to knock him down.

196
00:12:56,108 --> 00:12:59,904
That Lara, General Carillo's
adopted daughter.

197
00:12:59,987 --> 00:13:01,447
How is she?

198
00:13:01,530 --> 00:13:03,199
Aren't you always with her?

199
00:13:03,282 --> 00:13:05,493
Sir, I'm sticking close to her

200
00:13:05,576 --> 00:13:07,161
to keep a close eye on her moves.

201
00:13:08,162 --> 00:13:09,246
Good.

202
00:13:10,122 --> 00:13:11,582
Jalil, you have to remember.

203
00:13:12,249 --> 00:13:15,461
If General Carillo is the mastermind

204
00:13:15,544 --> 00:13:18,506
behind the massacre
of your people and NLEA,

205
00:13:18,589 --> 00:13:23,135
that means Lara is an accomplice.

206
00:13:23,636 --> 00:13:25,554
She's definitely involved.

207
00:13:25,638 --> 00:13:27,973
[tense music continues]

208
00:13:29,725 --> 00:13:30,893
[Espina] Thank you, sir.

209
00:13:32,520 --> 00:13:33,896
Thank you very much.

210
00:13:33,979 --> 00:13:35,648
[Ahmad] To all of you, thank you so much.

211
00:13:35,731 --> 00:13:38,734
To all the officials, thank you so much.

212
00:13:38,817 --> 00:13:41,612
Thank you so much, Task Force Alpha.

213
00:13:42,238 --> 00:13:43,739
[in Tausug] Thank you so much. Thank you.

214
00:13:44,448 --> 00:13:45,991
[Datu Rahman and Jamilah in Tausug]
Thank you.

215
00:13:47,701 --> 00:13:49,286
- [in Tausug] Thank you.
- Thank you so much.

216
00:13:49,370 --> 00:13:52,039
["Maninindigan" by Marko Rudio playing]

217
00:14:17,940 --> 00:14:20,860
[reporter 2] Sir Mustapha,
now that the scalawags

218
00:14:20,943 --> 00:14:22,444
in NLEA who were in cahoots
and were protecting

219
00:14:22,528 --> 00:14:24,405
the syndicate have been captured,

220
00:14:24,488 --> 00:14:26,782
will the crime and chaos
finally come to an end?

221
00:14:27,366 --> 00:14:29,034
This is just the beginning.

222
00:14:29,118 --> 00:14:32,371
There's still more cleaning
to do inside the agency.

223
00:14:32,454 --> 00:14:36,125
In NLEA, the SID, and the government.

224
00:14:36,208 --> 00:14:38,961
We won't stop here. We'll keep at it.

225
00:14:39,044 --> 00:14:42,548
[reporter 3] Sir,
has Jalil Abubakar's name been cleared?

226
00:14:42,631 --> 00:14:44,842
Because to this day, he's still in hiding.

227
00:14:44,925 --> 00:14:46,051
[camera shutters clicking]

228
00:14:46,135 --> 00:14:50,222
Perhaps he has his own reasons
for remaining in hiding.

229
00:14:50,306 --> 00:14:54,476
What matters is that his name
has been cleared

230
00:14:54,560 --> 00:14:57,646
and he can return home to his family.

231
00:14:57,730 --> 00:14:59,315
[reporter 4] Sir, where is he now?

232
00:14:59,398 --> 00:15:00,816
[reporter 5] How is his family?

233
00:15:00,900 --> 00:15:02,401
[reporter 4] Sir, what will be the…

234
00:15:03,694 --> 00:15:05,446
[tense music playing]

235
00:15:09,408 --> 00:15:11,493
Now that Datu Rahman Abubakar

236
00:15:11,577 --> 00:15:15,372
has been released from custody
and cleared from his charges,

237
00:15:15,456 --> 00:15:18,375
as well as the capture of the mastermind

238
00:15:18,459 --> 00:15:20,586
behind all the chaos and crimes,

239
00:15:20,669 --> 00:15:22,296
according to experts,

240
00:15:22,379 --> 00:15:25,633
this is a sign indicating
that peace and order

241
00:15:25,716 --> 00:15:27,009
will finally return to our country.

242
00:15:27,092 --> 00:15:29,720
It is also expected that the government

243
00:15:29,803 --> 00:15:31,013
will finally shut down

244
00:15:31,096 --> 00:15:33,641
the huge syndicate that's behind

245
00:15:33,724 --> 00:15:36,852
the distribution and sale
of illegal firearms

246
00:15:36,936 --> 00:15:39,438
across the Philippines.

247
00:15:39,521 --> 00:15:42,900
Finally, Father, we can be together again.

248
00:15:43,567 --> 00:15:46,612
And we don't have to hide
from anyone anymore.

249
00:15:47,863 --> 00:15:49,490
[in Arabic] Praise be to God.

250
00:15:49,573 --> 00:15:50,824
[in Arabic] Praise be to God.

251
00:15:50,908 --> 00:15:53,494
Good thing the truth came out.

252
00:15:53,577 --> 00:15:55,496
Your names have been cleared.

253
00:15:55,579 --> 00:15:56,997
That's right.

254
00:15:57,081 --> 00:15:59,708
But we lost a lot of time
together, didn't we?

255
00:15:59,792 --> 00:16:03,295
You've been in many precarious
situations too, Datu Rahman.

256
00:16:03,379 --> 00:16:06,757
A lot of people got involved too.

257
00:16:07,341 --> 00:16:10,052
That's why even though I've been released,

258
00:16:10,135 --> 00:16:12,888
I know it's not the end of it.

259
00:16:13,555 --> 00:16:17,810
We need to bring justice to the victims.

260
00:16:18,477 --> 00:16:20,020
I agree.

261
00:16:20,104 --> 00:16:22,856
But for now,
let's just be thankful to Allah

262
00:16:22,940 --> 00:16:24,400
that we're finally together again.

263
00:16:24,483 --> 00:16:27,778
Right. And let's go home
before the sun goes down.

264
00:16:27,861 --> 00:16:30,656
I'm sure you're all tired and hungry.

265
00:16:30,739 --> 00:16:32,574
- Well, then!
- Let's go!

266
00:16:35,828 --> 00:16:37,496
- This is missing something.
- Buy some, okay?

267
00:16:38,205 --> 00:16:39,873
- Sure thing!
- They're all freshly made!

268
00:16:39,957 --> 00:16:41,291
I'll get some later!

269
00:16:42,251 --> 00:16:43,752
[melancholic music playing]

270
00:16:44,378 --> 00:16:45,838
[Ibrahim] Norhana.

271
00:16:45,921 --> 00:16:48,090
You should tell them
to eat properly instead!

272
00:16:49,341 --> 00:16:51,218
Oh, it… it's Datu Rahman!

273
00:16:51,301 --> 00:16:53,053
Everyone, look! It's Datu Rahman!

274
00:16:53,137 --> 00:16:54,096
- Datu Rahman!
- [people clamoring]

275
00:16:54,179 --> 00:16:55,889
Ibrahim, it's Datu Rahman!

276
00:16:55,973 --> 00:16:58,225
- [people laughing, clamoring]
- [woman] It's Datu Rahman!

277
00:16:58,308 --> 00:17:00,728
- Hey!
- [in unison] Welcome back,

278
00:17:00,811 --> 00:17:02,646
Datu Rahman!

279
00:17:02,730 --> 00:17:05,190
[in Tausug] Thank you! Thank you.

280
00:17:05,274 --> 00:17:06,316
[poignant music playing]

281
00:17:08,277 --> 00:17:10,446
- Oh! Huh?
- Datu Rahman!

282
00:17:10,529 --> 00:17:11,780
- Aw!
- [laughter]

283
00:17:11,864 --> 00:17:13,073
Who's this little shrimp, huh?

284
00:17:13,157 --> 00:17:14,450
- [laughing]
- [Datu Rahman] Let me see!

285
00:17:14,533 --> 00:17:18,203
- Sitti! How did you get here, huh?
- [Jamilah laughing]

286
00:17:22,374 --> 00:17:24,376
Come here, you!

287
00:17:24,460 --> 00:17:27,171
[somber music playing]

288
00:17:35,262 --> 00:17:36,680
Alright then!

289
00:17:36,764 --> 00:17:38,766
- I'll cook your favorite dish
- Oh!

290
00:17:38,849 --> 00:17:41,518
because I'm sure
you miss Zamboangan cuisine.

291
00:17:41,602 --> 00:17:42,936
- Alright!
- [applauding, cheering]

292
00:17:43,020 --> 00:17:44,438
I'll go cook some!

293
00:17:46,482 --> 00:17:48,692
- Come on!
- Hey, it better be for free!

294
00:17:48,776 --> 00:17:50,110
- It's free!
- Free food!

295
00:17:50,194 --> 00:17:51,445
It's sure to be yummy!

296
00:17:51,528 --> 00:17:52,696
[indistinct chattering]

297
00:17:52,780 --> 00:17:54,740
[Norhana] I was hoping
I could borrow some…

298
00:17:54,823 --> 00:17:56,700
[Ibrahim laughs]

299
00:18:02,498 --> 00:18:05,459
Son, I saw the news earlier.

300
00:18:05,542 --> 00:18:07,544
Datu Rahman is finally free.

301
00:18:07,628 --> 00:18:09,838
He's finally together with Jamilah.

302
00:18:10,672 --> 00:18:11,715
[Marcus puffs]

303
00:18:11,799 --> 00:18:15,177
I told you, you'll be able
to solve this case, didn't I?

304
00:18:15,260 --> 00:18:17,221
[poignant music playing]

305
00:18:24,686 --> 00:18:27,314
Whatever you see on the news
isn't true, Ma.

306
00:18:27,397 --> 00:18:29,608
[pensive music playing]

307
00:18:31,068 --> 00:18:33,070
It isn't over just yet.

308
00:18:34,279 --> 00:18:36,573
What do you mean, son?

309
00:18:36,657 --> 00:18:40,119
[stirring music playing]

310
00:18:40,202 --> 00:18:43,622
We still haven't found
the real mastermind behind all this.

311
00:18:45,874 --> 00:18:49,253
Valdez and Yulo, all of them,
are just the tip of the iceberg.

312
00:18:51,171 --> 00:18:53,632
Espina thinks so too.
We're on the same page.

313
00:18:54,508 --> 00:18:57,427
For now, they can still toy
with the public.

314
00:18:57,970 --> 00:19:00,389
But everything that's happening right now

315
00:19:01,223 --> 00:19:04,101
is part of the syndicate's grand scheme.

316
00:19:06,687 --> 00:19:08,897
There is an even greater danger
rearing its head.

317
00:19:09,565 --> 00:19:11,817
[stirring music continues]

318
00:19:15,279 --> 00:19:18,574
If they're able to create
a scheme as huge as this,

319
00:19:18,657 --> 00:19:23,078
it means that what they're planning
is far greater and more dangerous.

320
00:19:28,750 --> 00:19:29,877
[sighs]

321
00:19:43,098 --> 00:19:44,349
[joyous sighs]

322
00:19:47,144 --> 00:19:48,604
- [Datu Rahman] Jamilah!
- Father.

323
00:19:51,648 --> 00:19:53,025
A change of clothes, Father.

324
00:19:53,108 --> 00:19:55,694
- [in Tausug] Thank you.
- A blanket, towel.

325
00:20:00,908 --> 00:20:02,618
- Jalil.
- Jamilah.

326
00:20:02,701 --> 00:20:04,244
- Jalil.
- Jalil!

327
00:20:04,328 --> 00:20:05,454
[Datu Rahman sobs softly]

328
00:20:05,537 --> 00:20:08,665
[poignant music playing]

329
00:20:08,749 --> 00:20:10,042
[Jalil] Father.

330
00:20:17,216 --> 00:20:18,675
I am beyond grateful.

331
00:20:19,676 --> 00:20:21,553
Because of your sacrifice,

332
00:20:22,429 --> 00:20:24,389
my name has been cleared.

333
00:20:25,390 --> 00:20:27,226
[in Tausug] Thank you, my son.

334
00:20:30,479 --> 00:20:34,316
Jalil, we can go back to the island.

335
00:20:35,067 --> 00:20:37,110
Back to our old life.

336
00:20:37,194 --> 00:20:39,071
You don't have to pretend anymore.

337
00:20:39,863 --> 00:20:42,115
You and Father are free.

338
00:20:42,199 --> 00:20:45,994
[sighs]

339
00:20:46,078 --> 00:20:47,579
We can't go back yet.

340
00:20:48,538 --> 00:20:49,790
I'm not done with my mission.

341
00:20:52,960 --> 00:20:55,545
What are you talking about?

342
00:20:56,255 --> 00:21:00,550
Father, the suspects in NLEA's custody,

343
00:21:01,260 --> 00:21:02,719
I think they're part of the syndicate,

344
00:21:02,803 --> 00:21:06,473
but they're not the masterminds.

345
00:21:07,057 --> 00:21:10,102
There's someone higher up,
someone more powerful,

346
00:21:10,185 --> 00:21:11,687
pulling the strings.

347
00:21:12,938 --> 00:21:14,815
Father… [breathes heavily]

348
00:21:15,774 --> 00:21:16,858
[soft sobs] Jalil.

349
00:21:18,402 --> 00:21:22,781
It is enough for me
that we are together again.

350
00:21:23,448 --> 00:21:26,535
Let's go back home.

351
00:21:26,618 --> 00:21:28,662
I'm scared, son.

352
00:21:29,413 --> 00:21:30,998
The longer you stay here,

353
00:21:32,124 --> 00:21:35,085
the more you're putting
your life in danger.

354
00:21:35,669 --> 00:21:36,962
Jalil.

355
00:21:37,713 --> 00:21:38,922
Father is right.

356
00:21:40,132 --> 00:21:43,385
What if they find out who you really are?

357
00:21:43,468 --> 00:21:45,846
[morose music playing]

358
00:21:46,972 --> 00:21:48,849
Jamilah, Father.

359
00:21:50,851 --> 00:21:53,729
I promised I wouldn't go home

360
00:21:54,813 --> 00:22:00,402
until I get real justice for our people.

361
00:22:00,485 --> 00:22:03,155
[Jalil sighs]

362
00:22:07,367 --> 00:22:10,704
I'm keeping that promise,
no matter what happens.

363
00:22:13,790 --> 00:22:17,544
[suspenseful music playing]

364
00:22:55,165 --> 00:22:57,167
[Usman] <i>You and Jamilah can't be together.</i>

365
00:22:57,250 --> 00:22:58,251
Why do you say that?

366
00:22:58,335 --> 00:23:02,547
Islamic law does not permit a Muslim woman
to marry a non-Muslim man.

367
00:23:02,631 --> 00:23:05,258
[Lara] <i>Why'd you make me your partner?</i>
<i>Are you trying to piss me off?</i>

368
00:23:05,342 --> 00:23:07,260
You don't want people to see you need help

369
00:23:07,344 --> 00:23:08,929
because you don't want them
to think you're weak.

370
00:23:09,012 --> 00:23:11,223
I am perfectly capable on my own.
I don't need any help.

371
00:23:11,765 --> 00:23:14,768
[Azuelo] <i>Heightened police presence</i>
<i>is required</i>

372
00:23:14,851 --> 00:23:18,063
<i>around NLEA and SID premises.</i>

373
00:23:18,146 --> 00:23:20,148
- Whose idea is this, sir?
- General Carillo's.

374
00:23:20,232 --> 00:23:22,651
[Jalil] <i>I hope you're not</i>
<i>an accomplice, Lara.</i>

375
00:23:22,734 --> 00:23:24,361
<i>I don't want you to get dragged into this.</i>

376
00:23:24,444 --> 00:23:26,363
[Ahmad] <i>General Carillo</i>
<i>personally requested</i>

377
00:23:26,446 --> 00:23:28,240
<i>that we keep an eye on investors.</i>

378
00:23:28,323 --> 00:23:34,037
[in English] This is going to be
the best day of my life!

379
00:23:35,080 --> 00:23:36,957
[in Japanese] <i>General Carillo!</i>

380
00:23:37,040 --> 00:23:38,542
- [in Japanese] Hello.
- <i>Hello.</i>

381
00:23:38,625 --> 00:23:39,793
[in English] It's an honor to meet you.

382
00:23:40,335 --> 00:23:44,798
What are you planning
this time, General Carillo?

383
00:23:45,966 --> 00:23:47,884
[action music playing]
